# Next.js 16 auto-regenerates next-env.d.ts with different content between
# `pnpm dev` (writes .next/dev/types/routes.d.ts reference) and `pnpm build`
# (writes .next/types/routes.d.ts reference). Next's official docs say to
# commit this file, but in 16.x that makes the working tree perpetually
# dirty for anyone running both commands locally. Ignored here until Next
# stabilizes the path. TypeScript types still resolve correctly at build time.
next-env.d.ts

# Claude Code — not tracked in template. Fork consumers run their own
# sessions with their own settings.
.claude/

# Raw client-provided images (phone/camera originals). Process through
# `pnpm images:prep` — optimized variants land in public/images/ and ARE
# committed; the multi-MB originals are not.
raw-assets/
